Privacy Policy
The current privacy policy describes the way Litera Games («we»), mobile apps developer, collects, uses and shares your data while you use our apps.
This page is used to inform visitors regarding our
                  policies with the collection, use, and disclosure of Personal
                  Information if anyone decided to use our Service.
If you choose to use our Service, then you agree to
                  the collection and use of information in relation to this
                  policy. The Personal Information that we collect is
                  used for providing and improving the Service. We will not use or share your information with
                  anyone except as described in this Privacy Policy.
The terms used in this Privacy Policy have the same meanings
                  as in our Terms and Conditions, which is accessible at
                  the app unless otherwise defined in this Privacy Policy.
Information Collection and Use
We collect anonymous app launches data, the sessions frequency and duration, passing levels, making purchases, failures and other events while using the app. Such statistics contribute to the apps improvement, hereby making it more interesting and fun. The events are collected while using one or more of such services including such as Google Analytics, Yandex AppMetrica (see Details).
We use unique Google Advertising ID or IDFA device identifiers to work with ad networks, personalizing the displayed ads. You may disable the ads personalization in your device’s settings. Besides you may disable ad impressions in the app by purchasing the ads disabling in the store (if the app supports ads disabling).
We get the country’s name and approximate location, which doesn’t allow us to determine your exact location, to personalize advertising and analytics.
